# .trivyignore — accepted CVEs / misconfigs with justification
#
# Format: one CVE ID, misconfig ID, or secret rule ID per line. Blank lines and
# lines starting with "#" are ignored. Trailing "exp:YYYY-MM-DD" sets an
# expiry after which Trivy fails again so ignores do not rot silently.
#
# Policy:
#   - Every entry MUST have a justification comment on the line above it.
#   - Every entry MUST have an expiry no more than 90 days out.
#   - Prefer fixing over ignoring. If upstream has no fix, use --ignore-unfixed
#     (already set in the pipelines) instead of listing here.
#
# Examples (remove before use):
#
# # setuptools <70 RCE — mitigated: container runs as non-root `app` user and
# # pip install is never invoked at runtime. Re-evaluate when upstream ships a fix.
# CVE-2024-6345 exp:2026-07-01
#
# # Dockerfile misconfig: no HEALTHCHECK — false positive, we set HEALTHCHECK
# # in the Dockerfile but Trivy does not parse the CMD form correctly.
# AVD-DS-0026 exp:2026-07-01
